statement.p:
Consider the following network with V = \{ 1, 2, 3, 4 \} and E = \{ (1,2), (3,4) \}.
Confirm that the modularity scores of the following four partitions by filling in the summands for 1 \leq i,j \leq 4.

Use this link to a Google Sheet to speed up calculations. Pay attention to the modularity contributions for various pairs of nodes. In particular, when i and j are in different communities, the corresponding summand is zero.








 A single community.



\begin{tikzpicture} %mathbook width=40%

\draw [rounded corners,fill=gray!20] (-.33, -.75) z-z-z (1.33, -.75) z-z-z (1.33,1.75) z-z-z (-.33, 1.75) z-z-z cycle;

\node at (3,.5) {Q \, = \, 0};

\draw[very thick] (0,0) z-z-z (0,1);
\draw[very thick] (1,0) z-z-z (1,1);

\draw[fill] (0,0) circle (3pt);
\draw[fill] (1,0) circle (3pt);
\draw[fill] (0,1) circle (3pt);
\draw[fill] (1,1) circle (3pt);

\node[above=3pt] at (0,1) {1};
\node[below=3pt] at (0,0) {2};
\node[above=3pt] at (1,1) {3};
\node[below=3pt] at (1,0) {4};





\end{tikzpicture}





















